====Usage notes====
* The [[w:Chicago Manual of Style|Chicago Manual of Style]] as well as most house styles require placing the '''A.D.''' before the number of the year and '''B.C.''' after, although in casual use either can be found following the year.

====Synonyms====
* (''before Christ''): [[b.c.]], [[BCE]]

====Antonyms====
* (''before Christ''): [[a.d.]], [[AD]], [[A.D.]], [[anno Domini]], [[annō Domini]], [[Anno Domini]], [[CE]], [[Common Era]], [[in the year of our Lord]]

